Description: Cylinder jar of calcite with concave sides and a rounded rim, below which there is a band of cord decoration. Interior completely hollowed.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tomb of Qaa, tomb Q.21 subsidiary burial
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, 28, pl. XXXVIII, 8.
